  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding Requirement mandates controlled-experiment verification of the hemolysis model against in-vitro bench data collected under tightly regulated flow and speed conditions. Supporting validation evidence was gathered via a prospective observational study of pump operating data drawn from a multi-site clinical registry; the study narrative describes careful flow-rate stratification and speed-matched cohort selection, presenting the evidence as functionally equivalent to bench experimentation. However, the structured activityType of the generating Activity is 'observational-study', not 'controlled-experiment' as required, breaking the inference link between the Requirement and the ValidationResult. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; six achieve required levels and seven fall short, consistent with MRL 5 expectations. Decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-controlled-experiment",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
