      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Multi-site registry hemolysis validation result",
      "description": "Hemolysis index values predicted by the CFD model were compared against plasma-free hemoglobin measurements collected from a five-center clinical registry of VAD patients. Operating conditions (flow rate 4–6 L/min, speed 2400–3200 RPM) were stratified into five speed-matched cohorts to align with the five COU operating points. Agreement between CFD-predicted hemolysis index and registry-derived hemolysis index was within 18% across all cohorts, which the assessment team characterised as satisfactory given the heterogeneity of patient haematocrit. The study design included propensity-score matching to control for confounders and is considered by the authors to provide evidence of equivalent rigour to bench experimentation. This result is cited as the primary validation evidence satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement of REQ-VAD-HEM-01.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
