      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification result — hemolysis index",
      "description": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed over 2000 samples of inlet boundary conditions, fluid viscosity, and power-law hemolysis model constants. 95th-percentile hemolysis index remained below the clinical threshold of 0.01 g/dL across all five operating points. Sensitivity indices (Sobol first-order) indicate that hemolysis model constant k accounts for 62% of output variance, flagging model-form uncertainty as the dominant epistemic gap.",
